  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Current state: zero tests.** No `tests/` directory, no pytest config, no CI workflow. All 1,430 lines across 7 modules (`models.py`, `filters.py`, `store.py`, `notify.py`, `fetchers.py`, `pipeline.py`, `cli.py`, `agent.py`) are completely untested. This is a from-scratch coverage plan, prioritized by risk (parsing logic that silently produces wrong data is riskier than argparse wiring).\n\nRecommended setup: `pytest`, `pytest-asyncio`, `respx` (for mocking `httpx`), `freezegun` or manual UTC-clock injection for time-dependent tests. Suggested layout: `tests/test_models.py`, `tests/test_filters.py`, `tests/test_store.py`, `tests/test_notify.py`, `tests/test_fetchers.py` (one class per ATS), `tests/test_pipeline.py`, `tests/test_agent.py`, `tests/conftest.py`.\n\n---\n\n### 1. `models.py` — highest priority, zero coverage\n\n**Untested: `parse_posted_at`**, the trickiest function in the codebase (multi-format, silent-failure-by-design).\n\nGaps:\n- Millisecond epoch (Lever, 13 digits) vs second epoch vs negative/zero epoch\n- ISO-8601 with `Z` suffix, with offset, without timezone (naive → should become UTC)\n- Empty string, `None`-like falsy input, garbage string → must return `None`, not raise\n- Boundary at exactly `1_000_000_000_000` (ms/s cutoff)\n\n**Untested: `Job.key`, `Job.content_hash`, `Job.to_row`**\n- `content_hash` must change when title/location/url/department change, and stay stable when other fields (e.g. `posted_at`) change\n- `to_row` must drop `raw` and add `key`/`content_hash`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_none_and_empty_return_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n        assert parse_posted_at(None) is None  # type: ignore[arg-type]\n\n    def test_garbage_string_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"not a date\") is None\n\n    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\"epoch_ms,expected_year\", [\n        (\"1643241332430\", 2022),\n    ])\n    def test_lever_millisecond_epoch(self, epoch_ms, expected_year):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(epoch_ms)\n        assert dt.year == expected_year\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_second_epoch_boundary_just_under_ms_cutoff(self):\n        # 999_999_999_999 is 12 digits -> should be treated as seconds\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"999999999999\")\n        assert dt is not None\n\n    def test_iso8601_with_z_suffix(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\")\n        assert dt == datetime(2024, 1, 15, 10, 0, tzinfo=timezone.utc)\n\n    def test_iso8601_naive_gets_utc_attached(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_iso8601_with_explicit_offset_preserved(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00+05:00\")\n        assert dt.utcoffset().total_seconds() == 5 * 3600\n\n    def test_workday_prose_string_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    def test_negative_epoch(self):\n        # lstrip(\"-\").isdigit() branch — pre-1970 dates\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"-100\")\n        assert dt is not None\n\n\nclass TestJobKey:\n    def test_key_is_stable_across_field_edits(self):\n        j = Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"A\", url=\"u\")\n        key = j.key\n        j.title = \"B\"\n        assert j.key == key\n\n    def test_key_differs_by_source_company_or_id(self):\n        base = dict(title=\"A\", url=\"u\")\n        a = Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", **base)\n        b = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", **base)\n        assert a.key != b.key\n\n\nclass TestContentHash:\n    def test_changes_when_title_changes(self):\n        j = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"A\", url=\"u\")\n        h1 = j.content_hash\n        j.title = \"B\"\n        assert j.content_hash != h1\n\n    def test_stable_when_posted_at_or_salary_changes(self):\n        j = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"A\", url=\"u\")\n        h1 = j.content_hash\n        j.posted_at = \"2024-01-01\"\n        j.salary_range = \"$100k\"\n        assert j.content_hash == h1\n\n\nclass TestToRow:\n    def test_drops_raw_and_adds_key_and_hash(self):\n        j = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"A\", url=\"u\",\n                raw={\"secret\": True})\n        row = j.to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert row[\"key\"] == j.key\n        assert row[\"content_hash\"] == j.content_hash\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `filters.py` — no coverage\n\nGaps:\n- Word-boundary regex behavior (`\\b`) — e.g. include `\"eng\"` should NOT match `\"engineering\"` substring inside a larger word incorrectly, but should match `\"Engineer\"` as a whole word\n- `include`/`exclude` interaction ordering (exclude checked first — a job matching both should be excluded)\n- Case-insensitivity\n- `locations` substring matching (not word-boundary, different logic path)\n- `cutoff` behavior for unparseable `posted_at` (must be **kept**, not dropped) — this is an explicit design decision worth locking in with a test\n- `filter_jobs` builds `cutoff` from `max_age_days`; untested for `0`, missing, and float values\n- Empty `rules` dict → passthrough\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\n\ndef _job(title=\"Software Engineer\", dept=\"Eng\", loc=\"Remote - US\", posted_at=\"\"):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=title, url=\"u\",\n               department=dept, location=loc, posted_at=posted_at)\n\n\nclass TestMatch:\n    def test_no_rules_passes(self):\n        assert match(_job()) is True\n\n    def test_include_keyword_matches_whole_word_only(self):\n        assert match(_job(title=\"Senior Engineer\"), include=[\"engineer\"]) is True\n        assert match(_job(title=\"Engineering Manager\"), include=[\"engineer\"]) is False\n\n    def test_include_keyword_case_insensitive(self):\n        assert match(_job(title=\"ENGINEER\"), include=[\"engineer\"]) is True\n\n    def test_exclude_takes_priority_over_include(self):\n        j = _job(title=\"Senior Engineer\", dept=\"Sales\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"engineer\"], exclude=[\"senior\"]) is False\n\n    def test_locations_is_substring_not_word_boundary(self):\n        assert match(_job(loc=\"San Francisco, CA\"), locations=[\"francisco\"]) is True\n\n    def test_locations_no_match_excludes(self):\n        assert match(_job(loc=\"London, UK\"), locations=[\"new york\"]) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_drops_confirmed_old_posting(self):\n        old = _job(posted_at=\"2020-01-01T00:00:00Z\")\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)\n        assert match(old, cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_posted_at(self):\n        j = _job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\")  # Workday prose, unparseable\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n        assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_recent_posting(self):\n        j = _job(posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)\n        assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n\nclass TestFilterJobs:\n    def test_empty_rules_returns_all(self):\n        jobs = [_job(), _job(external_id=\"2\")]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n\n    def test_max_age_days_builds_cutoff(self):\n        old = _job(posted_at=\"2000-01-01T00:00:00Z\")\n        result = filter_jobs([old], {\"max_age_days\": 1})\n        assert result == []\n\n    def test_max_age_days_zero_is_falsy_and_ignored(self):\n        # rules.get(\"max_age_days\") truthiness check: 0 is falsy -> no cutoff applied\n        old = _job(posted_at=\"2000-01-01T00:00:00Z\")\n        result = filter_jobs([old], {\"max_age_days\": 0})\n        assert result == [old]\n```\n\nNote the `max_age_days: 0` case above is a genuine **gap in the implementation, not just tests** — `if max_age:` treats `0` as \"no filter,\" which may or may not be intended. Worth flagging to whoever owns this file.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `store.py` — no coverage, most integration-heavy module\n\nGaps:\n- `diff()`: new job inserted correctly; unchanged job only bumps `last_seen`; changed job (different `content_hash`) updates fields and appears in `changed`\n- Migration path: opening a pre-existing DB file without `salary_range` column (simulate old schema)\n- `get_meta`/`set_meta`: missing key returns `None`; upsert overwrites existing value\n- `added_since`: string-comparison ordering assumption — verify ordering by `first_seen, company, title`\n- `count()`\n- Context manager (`__enter__`/`__exit__`) actually closes connection\n- Concurrent/duplicate keys within a single `diff()` call (same job twice in one batch — is second occurrence treated as \"already seen\" within the same run since first was just inserted?)\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport sqlite3\nimport pytest\nfrom models import Job\nfrom store import Store\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"jobs.db\") as s:\n        yield s\n\n\ndef _job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"A\", loc=\"Remote\"):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=ext_id,\n               title=title, url=\"u\", location=loc)\n\n\nclass TestDiff:\n    def test_new_job_is_inserted_and_returned_as_new(self, store):\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n        assert len(new) == 1 and changed == []\n        assert store.count() == 1\n\n    def test_unchanged_job_on_second_run_is_neither_new_nor_changed(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n        assert new == [] and changed == []\n\n    def test_changed_content_updates_and_is_reported(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job(title=\"Old Title\")])\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job(title=\"New Title\")])\n        assert new == []\n        assert len(changed) == 1\n        row = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT title FROM jobs WHERE key=?\",\n                                  (changed[0].key,)).fetchone()\n        assert row[\"title\"] == \"New Title\"\n\n    def test_posted_at_only_change_does_not_trigger_changed(self, store):\n        j1 = _job()\n        store.diff([j1])\n        j2 = _job()\n        j2.posted_at = \"2024-01-01\"  # not part of content_hash\n        new, changed = store.diff([j2])\n        assert new == [] and changed == []\n\n    def test_duplicate_key_within_same_batch(self, store):\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job(), _job()])\n        # document actual behavior: second occurrence treated as already-seen\n        assert store.count() == 1\n\n\nclass TestMeta:\n    def test_get_meta_missing_key_returns_none(self, store):\n        assert store.get_meta(\"nope\") is None\n\n    def test_set_then_get_meta_roundtrip(self, store):\n        store.set_meta(\"last_scan\", \"2024-01-01T00:00:00\")\n        assert store.get_meta(\"last_scan\") == \"2024-01-01T00:00:00\"\n\n    def test_set_meta_overwrites_existing(self, store):\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v2\")\n        assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v2\"\n\n\nclass TestAddedSince:\n    def test_orders_by_first_seen_company_title(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"Z\"), _job(ext_id=\"2\", title=\"A\")])\n        rows = store.added_since(\"1970-01-01T00:00:00\")\n        assert [r[\"title\"] for r in rows] == sorted(r[\"title\"] for r in rows)\n\n    def test_excludes_rows_at_or_before_timestamp(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        ts = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()[0]\n        assert store.added_since(ts) == []\n\n\nclass TestMigration:\n    def test_opens_legacy_db_missing_salary_range_column(self, tmp_path):\n        path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n        conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n        conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n            CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n                external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT,\n                department TEXT, employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT,\n                content_hash TEXT, first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n        \"\"\")\n        conn.commit()\n        conn.close()\n        with Store(path) as s:\n            cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n            assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n\n\nclass TestContextManager:\n    def test_exit_closes_connection(self, tmp_path):\n        s = Store(tmp_path / \"j.db\")\n        with s:\n            pass\n        with pytest.raises(sqlite3.ProgrammingError):\n            s.conn.execute(\"SELECT 1\")\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `notify.py` — no coverage, error-handling-critical (`dispatch` swallows exceptions)\n\nGaps:\n- Each notifier's env-var gate (missing var → no-op, no crash) — currently untested per-notifier\n- `notify_sms`/`notify_slack`/`notify_webhook`/`notify_email` should not fire HTTP calls when `new`/`changed` are both empty (even if env vars set)\n- `_sms_body` truncation logic at the `limit` boundary\n- `notify_email` auth branch (`SMTP_USER` set vs not)\n- **`dispatch`'s exception isolation**: one notifier raising must not stop the others — this is the most important behavioral contract in the file and has zero coverage\n- `notify_sms` calls `resp.raise_for_status()` — an HTTP error here must be caught by `dispatch`, not propagate\n\n```python\n# tests/test_notify.py\nimport httpx\nimport pytest\nimport respx\nfrom models import Job\nimport notify\n\n\ndef _job(title=\"Eng\", company=\"acme\"):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=company, external_id=\"1\", title=title, url=\"u\")\n\n\nclass TestNotifyConsole:\n    def test_prints_no_fresh_listings_when_empty(self, capsys):\n        notify.notify_console([], [])\n        assert \"No fresh listings\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n    def test_prints_new_and_changed_sections(self, capsys):\n        notify.notify_console([_job()], [_job(title=\"Updated\")])\n        out = capsys.readouterr().out\n        assert \"NEW\" in out and \"UPDATED\" in out\n\n\nclass TestNotifySlack:\n    def test_noop_when_env_var_missing(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n        notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])  # must not raise / must not need network\n\n    @respx.mock\n    def test_noop_when_no_new_or_changed_even_if_configured(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.test/x\")\n        route = respx.post(\"https://hooks.slack.test/x\")\n        notify.notify_slack([], [])\n        assert not route.called\n\n    @respx.mock\n    def test_posts_when_configured_and_has_new(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.test/x\")\n        route = respx.post(\"https://hooks.slack.test/x\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200))\n        notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])\n        assert route.called\n\n\nclass TestSmsBody:\n    def test_truncates_at_limit_with_more_count(self):\n        jobs = [_job(title=f\"T{i}\") for i in range(10)]\n        body = notify._sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n        assert \"+2 more\" in body\n\n    def test_no_more_line_when_under_limit(self):\n        body = notify._sms_body([_job()], [], limit=8)\n        assert \"more\" not in body\n\n\nclass TestNotifySms:\n    def test_noop_when_any_of_four_env_vars_missing(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\")\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", raising=False)\n        notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])  # must not raise\n\n    @respx.mock\n    def test_raises_on_twilio_error_response(self, monkeypatch):\n        for k, v in dict(TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=\"sid\", TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=\"tok\",\n                          TWILIO_FROM=\"+1\", TWILIO_TO=\"+2\").items():\n            monkeypatch.setenv(k, v)\n        respx.post(url__regex=r\".*Messages\\.json\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(401))\n        with pytest.raises(httpx.HTTPStatusError):\n            notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])\n\n\nclass TestDispatch:\n    def test_one_notifier_failing_does_not_block_others(self, monkeypatch, capsys):\n        def boom(new, changed):\n            raise RuntimeError(\"boom\")\n        monkeypatch.setattr(notify, \"NOTIFIERS\", [boom, notify.notify_console])\n        notify.dispatch([], [])\n        out = capsys.readouterr().out\n        assert \"notifier boom failed\" in out\n        assert \"No fresh listings\" in out\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `fetchers.py` — largest file, no coverage; split into three risk tiers\n\n**Tier A — parsers (pure functions, easiest and highest-value to test).** Every `parse_*` needs missing-field defensiveness tests since these are hand-rolled against undocumented/positional payloads (`parse_google`, `parse_deshaw`, `parse_twosigma` especially — regex/positional parsing that silently degrades):\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_parsers.py\nfrom fetchers import (parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, parse_ashby, parse_google,\n                       parse_deshaw, parse_twosigma, parse_optiver, parse_meta,\n                       parse_microsoft, parse_netflix, parse_amazon, _extract_ds1,\n                       _amazon_posted_at, _lever_salary, _ashby_salary)\n\n\nclass TestParseGreenhouse:\n    def test_maps_core_fields(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"SWE\", \"absolute_url\": \"u\",\n                           \"location\": {\"name\": \"NYC\"},\n                           \"departments\": [{\"name\": \"Eng\"}, {\"name\": \"Core\"}],\n                           \"updated_at\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"}]}\n        [job] = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n        assert job.department == \"Eng, Core\"\n        assert job.external_id == \"1\"\n\n    def test_empty_jobs_list(self):\n        assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": []}) == []\n\n    def test_missing_location_object(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"SWE\", \"absolute_url\": \"u\"}]}\n        [job] = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n        assert job.location == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestLeverSalary:\n    def test_range_present_formats_with_commas(self):\n        j = {\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"USD 100,000–150,000\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_description_plain(self):\n        j = {\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"Competitive\"\n\n    def test_no_salary_info_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({}) == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestParseAshby:\n    def test_filters_unlisted_jobs(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"isListed\": False, \"title\": \"Hidden\"},\n                          {\"id\": \"2\", \"isListed\": True, \"title\": \"Visible\"}]}\n        result = parse_ashby(\"acme\", data)\n        assert len(result) == 1 and result[0].title == \"Visible\"\n\n\nclass TestExtractDs1AndParseGoogle:\n    def test_extract_ds1_missing_key_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _extract_ds1(\"<html>no data here</html>\") == []\n\n    def test_extract_ds1_malformed_json_returns_empty(self):\n        html = \"key: 'ds:1', data:[not valid json] , sideChannel\"\n        assert _extract_ds1(html) == []\n\n    def test_parse_google_skips_falsy_entries(self):\n        assert parse_google(\"google\", [None, [None]]) == []\n\n    def test_parse_google_short_arrays_dont_crash(self):\n        # array shorter than index 9/12 must not IndexError\n        result = parse_google(\"google\", [[\"id1\"]])\n        assert result[0].location == \"\"\n        assert result[0].posted_at == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestParseDeshaw:\n    def test_dedupes_repeated_job_ids(self):\n        page = ('<div data-job-id=\"1\"><span class=\"job-display-name\">A</span>'\n                '<span class=\"location\">NYC</span></div>' * 2)\n        result = parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", page)\n        assert len(result) == 1\n\n    def test_missing_title_or_id_skipped(self):\n        page = '<div data-job-id=\"1\"></div>'  # no title\n        assert parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", page) == []\n\n    def test_html_entities_unescaped_in_title_and_location(self):\n        page = ('<div data-job-id=\"1\"><span class=\"job-display-name\">R&amp;D Eng'\n                 '</span><span class=\"location\">S&atilde;o Paulo</span></div>')\n        [job] = parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", page)\n        assert job.title == \"R&D Eng\"\n\n\nclass TestAmazonPostedAt:\n    def test_valid_date_string(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n    def test_malformed_string_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"not a date\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_unknown_month_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"Frobtember 1, 2026\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_empty_string(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n```\n\n**Tier B — pagination loop logic** (`fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_optiver`, `fetch_microsoft`, `fetch_netflix`, `fetch_amazon`, `fetch_google`, `fetch_workday`). These share a \"stop when no fresh items\" pattern — untested for the `max_pages` safety cap actually engaging, and for a source that returns duplicate IDs across pages (would loop forever without the `seen` set — worth an explicit regression test):\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_pagination.py\nimport httpx\nimport pytest\nimport respx\nfrom fetchers import fetch_optiver, fetch_workday\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_fetch_optiver_stops_when_a_page_returns_no_fresh_items():\n    respx.get(\"https://www.optiver.com/en/api/v1/jobs\").mock(\n        return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"items\": []}))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_optiver(client, {\"company\": \"optiver\"})\n    assert jobs == []\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_fetch_optiver_respects_max_pages_cap():\n    respx.get(\"https://www.optiver.com/en/api/v1/jobs\").mock(\n        return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\n            \"items\": [{\"href\": \"/join-us/jobs/x-1\", \"title\": \"T\"}]}))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_optiver(client, {\"company\": \"optiver\", \"max_pages\": 2})\n    # same non-empty page repeats forever without a fresh-id check; regression\n    # guard on the pagination cap actually terminating the loop\n    assert len(jobs) <= 2\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_fetch_workday_stops_at_total_and_safety_cap():\n    respx.post(url__regex=r\".*/wday/cxs/.*\").mock(\n        return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobPostings\": [], \"total\": 0}))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_workday(client, {\"host\": \"h\", \"tenant\": \"t\", \"site\": \"s\"})\n    assert jobs == []\n```\n\n**Tier C — retry/error handling** (`_request`, `fetch_source`, `fetch_all`). This has the codebase's most important resilience contract and zero coverage:\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_resilience.py\nimport httpx\nimport pytest\nimport respx\nfrom fetchers import _request, fetch_source, fetch_all\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_request_retries_on_503_then_succeeds():\n    route = respx.get(\"https://x.test\").mock(side_effect=[\n        httpx.Response(503), httpx.Response(200, json={})])\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        r = await _request(client, \"https://x.test\", retries=3)\n    assert r.status_code == 200\n    assert route.call_count == 2\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_request_exhausts_retries_and_raises_runtime_error():\n    respx.get(\"https://x.test\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(500))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x.test\", retries=2)\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_source_unknown_ats_raises_value_error():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n            await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"bogus\"})\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_fetch_all_isolates_one_source_failure(monkeypatch, capsys):\n    respx.get(url__regex=r\".*boards-api\\.greenhouse\\.io.*\").mock(\n        return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"A\",\n                                                           \"absolute_url\": \"u\"}]}))\n    respx.get(url__regex=r\".*api\\.lever\\.co.*\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(500))\n    sources = [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"good\"},\n               {\"ats\": \"lever\", \"company\": \"bad\"}]\n    jobs = await fetch_all(sources, concurrency=2)\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n    assert \"failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_closes_owned_client_but_not_injected_one():\n    client = httpx.AsyncClient()\n    await fetch_all([], client=client)\n    assert not client.is_closed\n    await client.aclose()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `pipeline.py` — no coverage, main integration seam\n\nGaps:\n- `load_config` defaults (`sources`, `filters`, `db`, `concurrency`) applied when absent from YAML\n- `run(dry_run=True)` must not touch the `Store`/dedup state at all and must return `{\"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}` regardless of matches\n- `run` end-to-end with a fake fetcher (monkeypatch `fetch_all`) exercising fetch → filter → dedup → notify wiring\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest\nfrom pipeline import load_config, run\n\n\ndef test_load_config_applies_defaults(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    cfg = load_config(cfg_path)\n    assert cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\"\n    assert cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8\n    assert cfg[\"filters\"] == {}\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_dry_run_does_not_persist_or_notify(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    import pipeline\n    from models import Job\n\n    async def fake_fetch_all(sources, concurrency):\n        return [Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"A\", url=\"u\")]\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"fetch_all\", fake_fetch_all)\n\n    called = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"dispatch\", lambda n, c: called.append(True))\n\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(f\"sources: [{{}}]\\ndb: {tmp_path/'j.db'}\\n\")\n    result = await run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n\n    assert result == {\"matched\": 1, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n    assert not called\n    assert not (tmp_path / \"j.db\").exists()\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_full_run_persists_and_notifies(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    import pipeline\n    from models import Job\n\n    async def fake_fetch_all(sources, concurrency):\n        return [Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"A\", url=\"u\")]\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"fetch_all\", fake_fetch_all)\n    dispatched = {}\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"dispatch\",\n                         lambda n, c: dispatched.update(new=n, changed=c))\n\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(f\"sources: [{{}}]\\ndb: {tmp_path/'j.db'}\\n\")\n    result = await run(cfg_path, dry_run=False)\n\n    assert result == {\"matched\": 1, \"new\": 1, \"changed\": 0}\n    assert len(dispatched[\"new\"]) == 1\n    assert (tmp_path / \"j.db\").exists()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. `cli.py` — trivial but untested\n\n```python\n# tests/test_cli.py\nimport cli\n\n\ndef test_main_passes_config_and_dry_run_through(monkeypatch):\n    captured = {}\n    monkeypatch.setattr(cli, \"run_sync\",\n                         lambda path, dry_run: captured.update(path=path, dry_run=dry_run))\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\", \"-c\", \"custom.yaml\", \"--dry-run\"])\n    cli.main()\n    assert captured == {\"path\": \"custom.yaml\", \"dry_run\": True}\n\n\ndef test_main_defaults_config_path(monkeypatch):\n    captured = {}\n    monkeypatch.setattr(cli, \"run_sync\",\n                         lambda path, dry_run: captured.update(path=path, dry_run=dry_run))\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\"])\n    cli.main()\n    assert captured == {\"path\": \"sources.yaml\", \"dry_run\": False}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. `agent.py` — no coverage; two independently testable areas\n\n**`_normalize_ats`/`cmd_pdf_render`** — the char-replacement logic is pure and high-value to test in isolation (the \"never touch `<style>`/`<script>`/tags\" invariant is exactly the kind of thing that regresses silently):\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent_ats_normalize.py\nfrom agent import _normalize_ats\n\n\ndef test_replaces_smart_quotes_and_dashes_in_body_text():\n    html, counts = _normalize_ats(\"<p>“Hello” — world</p>\")\n    assert '\"Hello\" - world' in html\n    assert counts[\"smart-double-quote\"] == 2\n    assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\n\ndef test_does_not_touch_content_inside_style_or_script_tags(): \n    html, counts = _normalize_ats(\n        \"<style>content: '\\u2014';</style><p>\\u2014</p><script>var x='\\u2014';</script>\")\n    assert \"\\u2014\" in html.split(\"<p>\")[0]  # untouched inside <style>\n    assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1  # only the <p> occurrence counted\n\n\ndef test_does_not_touch_attribute_values_inside_tags():\n    html, counts = _normalize_ats('<a title=\"\\u2014\">text</a>')\n    assert 'title=\"\\u2014\"' in html  # attribute preserved\n    assert \"em-dash\" not in counts\n\n\ndef test_no_special_chars_returns_empty_counts():\n    html, counts = _normalize_ats(\"<p>plain text</p>\")\n    assert counts == {}\n```\n\n**`cmd_db_new`/`cmd_db_mark`** — first-run window logic, watermark truncation-at-group-boundary logic, and CLI arg validation are all untested:\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent_db_commands.py\nimport json\nimport pytest\nfrom agent import cmd_db_new, cmd_db_mark\nfrom store import Store\n\n\ndef test_db_mark_rejects_non_iso_watermark(capsys):\n    rc = cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-timestamp\"])\n    assert rc == 2\n    assert \"not an ISO timestamp\" in capsys.readouterr().err\n\n\ndef test_db_mark_requires_watermark_or_now(capsys):\n    rc = cmd_db_mark([])\n    assert rc == 2\n\n\ndef test_db_mark_now_and_explicit_watermark_persist(tmp_path):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    db = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"db: {db}\\n\")\n    cmd_db_mark([\"2024-01-01T00:00:00\", \"-c\", str(cfg)])\n    with Store(db) as s:\n        assert s.get_meta(\"last_scan\") == \"2024-01-01T00:00:00\"\n\n\ndef test_db_new_first_run_uses_since_days_window(tmp_path, capsys):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    db = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"db: {db}\\n\")\n    with Store(db):\n        pass\n    cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(cfg), \"--since-days\", \"3\"])\n    out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n    assert out[\"first_run\"] is True\n    assert out[\"count\"] == 0\n\n\ndef test_db_new_truncates_at_group_boundary_not_mid_group(tmp_path, capsys):\n    # verify: when limit falls inside a first_seen group, the whole group\n    # is dropped and watermark stays at the prior group's timestamp\n    ...\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary of gap priorities\n\n| Priority | Module | Why |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `models.parse_posted_at` | Silent-failure date parsing feeds the recency filter directly; wrong parsing = wrong drops |\n| 2 | `store.diff` | Core dedup correctness; a bug here duplicates or silently drops jobs |\n| 3 | `fetchers.py` parsers | Hand-parsed against undocumented APIs (Google `ds:1`, D.E. Shaw/Two Sigma regex scraping) — most likely to break on upstream changes, easiest to catch with fixtures |\n| 4 | `fetchers._request` retry + `fetch_all` isolation | The \"don't let one source kill the run\" contract has no regression test |\n| 5 | `notify.dispatch` isolation | Same failure-isolation contract, untested |\n| 6 | `filters.match` cutoff/keyword logic | Business-rule correctness, plus one real gap found (`max_age_days: 0` treated as disabled) |\n| 7 | `pipeline.run` | Integration test tying fetch→filter→dedup→notify together |\n| 8 | `agent.py` helpers | Lower risk (internal tooling), but `_normalize_ats` and watermark-truncation logic are non-trivial enough to deserve coverage |\n\n**Missing integration test entirely:** there's no test that runs the full pipeline against a live-shaped fixture (e.g., record one real Greenhouse/Lever response, replay it through `fetch_all` → `filter_jobs` → `Store.diff` → `dispatch`) to catch schema drift across the seam boundaries. Worth adding once the unit layer above exists.\n",
