        "content": "\n**Untested: `parse_posted_at`**, the trickiest function in the codebase (multi-format, silent-failure-by-design).\n\nGaps:\n- Millisecond epoch (Lever, 13 digits) vs second epoch vs negative/zero epoch\n- ISO-8601 with `Z` suffix, with offset, without timezone (naive → should become UTC)\n- Empty string, `None`-like falsy input, garbage string → must return `None`, not raise\n- Boundary at exactly `1_000_000_000_000` (ms/s cutoff)\n\n**Untested: `Job.key`, `Job.content_hash`, `Job.to_row`**\n- `content_hash` must change when title/location/url/department change, and stay stable when other fields (e.g. `posted_at`) change\n- `to_row` must drop `raw` and add `key`/`content_hash`\n\n```python\n",
