        "content": "\nGaps:\n- Word-boundary regex behavior (`\\b`) — e.g. include `\"eng\"` should NOT match `\"engineering\"` substring inside a larger word incorrectly, but should match `\"Engineer\"` as a whole word\n- `include`/`exclude` interaction ordering (exclude checked first — a job matching both should be excluded)\n- Case-insensitivity\n- `locations` substring matching (not word-boundary, different logic path)\n- `cutoff` behavior for unparseable `posted_at` (must be **kept**, not dropped) — this is an explicit design decision worth locking in with a test\n- `filter_jobs` builds `cutoff` from `max_age_days`; untested for `0`, missing, and float values\n- Empty `rules` dict → passthrough\n\n```python\n",
