on_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n```\n\n**Tier B — pagination loop logic** (`fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_optiver`, `fetch_microsoft`, `fetch_netflix`, `fetch_amazon`, `fetch_google`, `fetch_workday`). These share a \"stop when no fresh items\" pattern — untested for the `max_pages` safety cap actually engaging, and for a source that returns duplicate IDs across pages (would loop forever without the `seen` set — worth an explicit regression test):\n\n```python\n",
